05/10/2003
ROME, Italy -- Bulgarian Prime Minister Simeon Saxe-Coburg addressed the meeting of heads of state or government of the 15 EU members, 10 ascending states and three candidate countries in Rome on Saturday (4 October).
He urged participants not to offset the balance achieved so far and re-open negotiations on key provisions agreed upon in the Draft Constitution Treaty.
Saxe-Coburg also expressed satisfaction with his country's participation in an observer capacity, and said he was confident of full membership by 2007.
(BTA, Mediapool, bTV - 04/10/03)
